"after her meaning" - in her view, according to her opinion. "When the boys
would be here" = if the boys were here, they 2might1 (not could) eat as much
fruit. "May" signifies a permission from outward, "can" an inward possibil-
ity. I f.i. 2may1 eat all the butter in the kitchen, for who will prevent the
master of the house? - but I 2can1not eat it, as my stomach objects to it. I
estimate it very much, rather 2esteem1. An estimate is ein Anschlag (z.B. the
estimate for the building of a bridge at Calw amounts to 12100 Fl). - "I
like 2not1 very much" - The negation likes very much the verb to do. There-
fore: I do not like much - I like him, but I do not like his hat. "Almost
nothing than" - nothing but - "praying very zealous"-ly is most necessary




